def symmetric_difference_of_sets(set_m, set_n):
    """
    Calculate the symmetric difference of two sets of integers and return the result in ascending order.

    Parameters:
    set_m (list of int): The first set of integers.
    set_n (list of int): The second set of integers.

    Returns:
    list of int: The symmetric difference of the two sets, sorted in ascending order.
    """
    set_a = set(set_m)
    set_b = set(set_n)
    symmetric_diff = set_a | set_b
    return sorted(symmetric_diff)
